# Flutter Conventions

## State Management -- Riverpod

Use `hooks_riverpod` exclusively. The app is wrapped in `ProviderScope` in `main.dart`.

### Widget types:
- `ConsumerWidget` for stateless widgets that need providers
- `ConsumerStatefulWidget` for stateful widgets that need providers

### Provider types used:
- `StreamProvider` -- for Firestore document/collection streams (most data)
- `ChangeNotifierProvider` -- for `authProvider` (authentication state)
- `StateNotifierProvider` -- for `storiesProvider` (paginated feed)
- `StateProvider` -- for `pagingControllerProvider` (feed refresh)

### Accessing providers via extensions (from `extensions.dart`):

Use the `WidgetRef` extensions rather than raw `ref.watch`/`ref.read`:

```dart
// Stories, posts, statements, entities
ref.storyWatch(sid)       // AsyncValue<Story?>
ref.postWatch(pid)        // AsyncValue<Post?>
ref.statementsWatch(stids) // AsyncValue<List<Statement>?>
ref.entityWatch(eid)      // AsyncValue<Entity?>

// Auth
ref.authWatch             // Auth object
ref.isAdmin               // bool
ref.selfUserWatch()       // AsyncValue<ZUser?>
ref.user()                // ZUser (assumes logged in)

// Votes
ref.voteWatch(pid, uid, type) // AsyncValue<Vote?>
```

## Theming

Access colors via `BuildContext` extensions (from `extensions.dart`), NOT raw `Theme.of(context)`:

```dart
context.backgroundColor        // surface color
context.primaryColor            // primary color
context.secondaryColor          // green accent
context.errorColor              // purple (used for errors)
context.surfaceColor            // surfaceDim
context.onBackgroundColor       // onSurface
context.primaryColorWithOpacity // primary at 0.2 opacity
```

Color palette is in `constants.dart` (`Palette` class):
- `Palette.black`, `Palette.white`, `Palette.green`, `Palette.purple`, `Palette.red`, etc.

Two themes: `ZTheme.darkTheme` and `ZTheme.lightTheme`.
Dark mode check: `context.isDarkMode`.

## Spacing and Padding

Use `BuildContext` extensions (from `extensions.dart`), NOT raw `EdgeInsets` or `SizedBox`:

### Padding (EdgeInsets):
```dart
context.pf    // full padding (16 all sides)
context.ph    // half padding (8 all sides)
context.pq    // quarter padding (4 all sides)
context.pfh   // full horizontal, half vertical
context.pz    // zero padding
context.blockMargin   // quarter all sides (standard block margin)
context.blockPadding  // quarter all sides (standard block padding)
```

### SizedBox spacers:
```dart
context.sl    // least (2)
context.sq    // quarter (4)
context.sh    // half (8)
context.stq   // three-quarter (12)
context.sf    // full (16)
context.sth   // 1.5x (24)
context.sd    // double (32)
context.sfh   // 2.5x (40)
context.st    // triple (48)
context.sqd   // quadruple (64)
```

### Margin constants (`Margins` class in `constants.dart`):
- Base unit: `Margins.full = 16.0`
- Scale: `least` (2), `quarter` (4), `half` (8), `threeQuarter` (12), `full` (16), `twice` (32), `triple` (48), up to `octuple` (128)

## Typography

Access text styles via `BuildContext` extensions:

```dart
context.h1, context.h2, context.h3  // headlines
context.h4, context.h5, context.h6  // titles
context.l, context.m, context.s      // body (large, medium, small)
context.h1b, context.lb, context.mb  // bold variants
context.d1, context.d2, context.d3   // display styles
context.ah2, context.al, context.am  // "Minecart" font variants
```

Fonts: Georgia for display/headline, Avenir for body, Nunito as base.

## Components

All reusable components are prefixed with `Z` and live in `lib/common/components/`:

- `ZScaffold` -- app scaffold with safe area handling
- `ZAppBar` -- custom app bar
- `ZTextButton` -- styled text button
- `ZTextField` -- styled text input
- `ZListView` -- styled list view
- `ZDivider` -- styled divider
- `ZIconText` -- icon + text combo
- `ZTabBar` -- tab bar
- `ZExpansionTile` -- expandable tile
- `ZBackButton` -- back navigation
- `ZNavigationScaffold` -- navigation wrapper
- `ZError` -- error display

Other components (no Z prefix): `Loading`, `LoadingShimmer`, `ProfileIcon`, `Logo`, `Branding`, `ConfidenceComponent`, `PoliticalPositionComponent`, `StatsTable`, `ModalContainer`, `InfoView`, `TimeComponent`, `IconGrid`, `CommentWidget`, `LocationMap`

## Layout Constants

```dart
BRadius.standard  // 8px border radius (most common)
BRadius.steep     // 32px border radius
BRadius.circular  // 64px (fully rounded)
BRadius.little    // 4px
BRadius.least     // 2px

Curvature.standard // Radius.circular(8.0)

Thickness.least    // 0.25
Thickness.small    // 1.0
Thickness.standard // 1.5

IconSize.small     // 12.5
IconSize.standard  // 24.0
IconSize.large     // 33
```

## Responsive Design

Use `BuildContext` extensions:

```dart
context.isMobile         // width < 600
context.isTablet         // 600-1000
context.isDesktop        // width > 1000
context.isMobileOrTablet // < 1000
context.isWeb            // kIsWeb
context.isTrueMobile     // mobile + not web
context.blockSize        // responsive block size (max 800w, 16:9)
context.screenBlock      // full screen block with safe area
```

## Navigation

Use `GoRouter` via `BuildContext` extension:

```dart
context.route('/path')   // push if different from current
context.router           // GoRouter instance
context.currentLocation  // current path
```

## Modals and Toasts

```dart
context.showModal(widget)            // bottom sheet (mobile) or dialog (desktop)
context.showFullScreenModal(widget)  // full screen dialog
context.showToast('message')         // top toast notification
context.showToast('error', isError: true) // error toast
```

## General Rules

- Follow existing patterns rigorously
- Use `context.` extensions for all theming, spacing, and sizing
- Use `ref.` extensions for all provider access
- Prefix new reusable components with `Z`
- Place models in `lib/common/models/`
- Place services in `lib/common/services/`
- Place view screens in `lib/views/[feature]/`
- Use `const` constructors wherever possible
- Use FontAwesome icons (`FontAwesomeIcons.*`)
